    <stitle>HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS, AND BUMPER - PROSTAR&#8482; - REMOVE AND INSTALL PROCEDURES - FENDER EXTENSIONS
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="Remove and Install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>FENDER EXTENSIONS</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Fender Extensions - Removal</title>
            <figure id="f0901129" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901129.webp" type="webp" scalefitwidth="312px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 44. Left Fender Extension</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. LEFT FENDER EXTENSION</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. FENDER EXTENSION MOUNT BOLTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. FRONT MUD GUARD</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. MUD GUARD MOUNT BOLTS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Unlatch and open the hood.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Clean dirt and debris away from all mount hardware.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove six bolts and left fender extension from chassis.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0901130" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901130.webp" type="webp" scalefitwidth="312px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 45. Right Fender Extension</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. RIGHT FENDER EXTENSION</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. FENDER EXTENSION MOUNT BOLTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. MUD GUARD MOUNT BOLTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. FRONT MUD GUARD</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove five bolts and right fender extension from chassis.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To remove either front mud guard, remove four bolts and mud guard from fender
                    extension.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Fender Extensions - Installation</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To install either front mud guard, align the mud guard on the fender extension and
                    secure with four bolts, nuts, and eight washers (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901129">Figure 45, Items 3 and 4</hotlnk>) (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901130">Figure 45, Items 3 and 4</hotlnk>). Torque bolts to 14 to 18 lbf-ft (19 to
                    24 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install fender extension on chassis and align mounting holes.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Secure right fender extension with five bolts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901130">Figure 45, Items 1 and 2</hotlnk>). Torque bolts to 18 to 19 lbf-ft (24 to
                    26 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Secure left fender extension with six bolts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901129">Figure 44, Items 1 and 2</hotlnk>). Torque bolts to 18 to 19 lbf-ft (24 to
                    26 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Close hood and ensure fender extensions are aligned properly.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If either fender extension is not aligned properly, loosen mounting bolts, align fender
                    extension, and tighten bolts.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
